# Hybrid Test Automation Framework

## Project Overview

This project is a Hybrid Test Automation Framework developed using Selenium, Pytest, Requests, Jenkins, Docker, and Selenium Grid.

The framework automates:

- UI Testing
- API Testing
- End-to-End Validation
- Performance Checks
- Parallel Execution
- CI/CD Integration

The application under test is the Notes Application:
https://practice.expandtesting.com/notes/app

---

# Features Implemented

## UI Automation
- Login functionality validation
- Create note functionality
- Negative UI scenarios
- Screenshot capture on failure

## API Automation
- Login API
- Get Notes API
- Create Note API
- Delete Note API
- Negative API scenarios

## Hybrid Testing
- UI + API End-to-End validation

## Reporting
- HTML Reports
- Allure Reports

## Parallel Execution
- Implemented using pytest-xdist

## CI/CD
- Jenkins Pipeline Integration
- GitHub Integration

## Docker & Selenium Grid
- Selenium Hub setup
- Chrome Node execution
- Firefox Node execution
- Remote browser execution

## Agentic Automation
- Intelligent waiting system
- Auto-retry mechanism

## MCP Implementation Layer
- Simulated AI-based test data generation
- Failure analysis support
- Locator suggestion mechanism

## Performance Engineering
- API response time measurement
- UI page load timing
- Basic performance logging

